flowRoot.flowPara: "Senior Airman Revello’s positive and out-going attitude immediately impressed me and the entire training staff."
"Although extremely technically minded Evin has the ability to communicate with simple, friendly language with a great sense of humor."
"Evin is people-oriented and verbally fluent, it is these people skills that set her apart. She is great at creating enthusiasm in others!"

flowRoot.flowPara: Writing POSIX-compliant regular expresions which capture 911 automatic lookup information. Writing DML SQL scripts to deploy system configurations. Syncing data and confingurations from production to developement environments using the bcp utility of SQL Server and Redgate. Assessing data to measure accuracy, integrity, completeness, usefulness, and freshness using SQL Server and user-facing data sources available through ECaTS Reporting Software. Creating quality documentation, ranging from funtionality and nuances of the system to customer validation requests. Detecting, troubleshooting, and making recommendations on data quality issues by analyzing the data throughout each phase of the processing lifecycle; from data acquisition, build processing, and through to application use.

Wrote and edited user-facing documentation using Microsoft Word and Powerpoint in accordance with DoD style guides and preferences. Photoraphed products using a lean-lightbox techniques and edited in Adobe Photoshop to obscure proprietary implements. Interfaced with engineers to achieve factually accurate documentation. Created HTML5-compliant computer based training using Adobe Captivate. Performed quality assurance of hardware and software products, with a focus on consistent vernacular and system labeling.

Creation and modification of user interface elements using HTML, CSS, and JQuery. Graphic design accomplished using open-source tools such as Gimp, Inkscape, and Scribed. Dynamic web sites launched using the Wordpress CMS, including configurations and tweaks to the themes code-base. Performing routine devops maintenance of existing sites and applications. Crafting web experiences for clients which included documentation and hands-on-training when required. Utilizes elements of professional design to achieve functional form and stunning factor in visual documentation. Implemented small scale industrial-design solutions for horticulture startups. Reverse engineered functional requirements of serial communications command set of a electropherogram for a biotech startup.

Mastered the art of providing exceptional one-on-one customer service by anticipating customer needs and being able to suggest alternatives. Cross-functional coordination with members of management to meet retail and supply needs. Maintained cleanliness standards established by the Arkansas State Board of Health.

Operated and maintained a low pressure altitude chamber and life support systems which allowed for the simulation of altitudes of up to 35,000 feet in a training environment. Instructed five classes for aircrews; subjects included basic survival skills, parachute-landing familiarization, emergency egress procedures, life support systems, and the fundamentals of night vision. Prepared monthly training reports using Microsoft Access combined with the manual entry and manipulation of training events and any incidences that may have occurred. Documented and maintained records of over 50,000 flight crew members using Access for digital records and HIPPA-compliant procedures for the physical records. Operated and maintained ejection seat trainer capable of 7Gs as well as cockpit-egress mock-ups.
